text:
The Mets hope to open the short season in Queens on July 24 with a series against the Braves, health-permitting.

Four Braves recover from the coronavirusm including Freddie Freeman who had “body aches, headaches, chills and a high fever.”

text:
Friends and family of Jose Cepada — the first of 9 to die in a wave of Fourth of July weekend violence — took to social media to mourn, and condem the gun violence that took his life.

Cepada, 20, was shot to death in East New York.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Dr. Fauci said the country's “current state is really not good,” on the deadly coronavirus front. 

Before, the U.S. averaged 20,000 new cases a day. 

Then with reopenings, in a week and a half, cases jumped to nearly 58,000 a day. 
https://t.co/895wLoNNWL

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Anthony Rollo, a photo editor at the Daily News for more than 40 years, has died at 74.

Until 1991, the News called itself “New York’s Picture Newspaper,” and Rollo had a hand in most of the iconic covers from 9/11 to the blackout to infamous killers. 
https://t.co/3L6p48gsRS

name: NYDailyNews
text:
An American Airlines mechanic from Hicksville, L.I. was charged for his alleged role in a drug-trafficking scheme. 

A stash of cocaine was found under an airplane’s cockpit on a flight from Jamaica to JFK.
